+{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01BfBPhyZBmMaWekJcSopj9K","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"No checkpoint found. This is a non-interactive (headless benchmark) environment. The task is well-specified in the TASK.md — the spec defines exactly two functions with clear interfaces and a detailed example. The design is essentially given: simulate a circuit via topological ordering, and detect swapped wires by analyzing the structure of a ripple-carry adder.\n\nSince this is non-interactive, I'll use Autopilot mode and go straight to design, then implementation.\n\nThe key design decisions are straightforward from the spec:\n\n**simulate()**: Topological evaluation — repeatedly scan gates, fire any whose inputs are resolved, until all gates have fired.\n\n**findSwappedWires()**: Structural analysis of the ripple-carry adder pattern. Each bit position has a known structure (XOR for partial sum, XOR with carry for final sum, AND+AND+OR for carry chain). Walk the circuit bit by bit, checking that each gate's output matches the expected role. When a mismatch is found, identify the swap.\n\nLet me move directly to TDD implementation."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1401,"cache_read_input_tokens":23107,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1401},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d8fb5aef-4368-421c-b3e5-eaa1497c52be","uuid":"bbecea9c-274d-43bc-94c4-58f01b67b02e"}
